<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-08T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="821" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d821">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4529a:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-08T18:00:00-04:00">July
                                        8, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>36. Please inform the Department regarding the French Fleet in your
                                area, including particularly the units present and the attitude of
                                the officers and men. Information is also desired regarding alleged
                                fighting on the Syrian-Palestine border, regarding an announced
                                determination of the French authorities to defend Syria “against any
                                foreign encroachments”, and regarding Weygand’s present activities
                                and influence in Syria.</p>
                            <p>Keep the Department advised by frequent short telegrams at least
                                until the Franco-British situation is clarified.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>